00:45:26.820 --> 00:45:33.680
That sense, whether you like all of
it or not of being unquestionably

00:45:33.680 --> 00:45:38.320
at the center of the culture
is a very different thing,

00:45:38.320 --> 00:45:43.930
in a way that's it can though,
you know, less controlled

00:45:43.930 --> 00:45:47.190
to what were saying at the
beginning about the Museum

00:45:47.190 --> 00:45:50.670
of African American History
in the center of this nation.

00:45:50.670 --> 00:45:55.090
No one can deny whether it's, you
know, on the pages of a magazine

00:45:55.090 --> 00:46:00.520
or a newspaper or, you know, on
your computer that black culture

00:46:00.520 --> 00:46:04.430
in every way from rap to books

00:46:04.430 --> 00:46:09.190
to TV shows [inaudible]
is absolutely central

00:46:09.190 --> 00:46:12.100
to this thing we call
American culture.

00:46:12.100 --> 00:46:16.640
That gives you a very
different sense of yourself.

00:46:16.640 --> 00:46:22.640
It means you're not a footnote
or only a problem or a kind

00:46:22.640 --> 00:46:27.830
of supplicant or the forced--
forced to be always the rebel.

00:46:27.830 --> 00:46:30.390
You can still be all of those
things but you don't have

00:46:30.390 --> 00:46:33.050
to be a supplicant or
a footnote anymore.

